  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] If you have been in Israel, the road from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem, in the middle of the road when you travel, you have remains of trucks, which they used to build a cabin from metal to prevent bullets.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Jerusalem was surrendered.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Jordanian army did not allow to bring in food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They didn't have no water, no food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the order was at any price to open up the way to Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They did build a side road.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But they wanted to open up the main road, the way you'd go from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem, where those trucks are-- the remains of trucks are there-- to get in and break the line.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The assignment they gave me was I got nine trucks with 72 soldiers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Our equipment was machine guns and rifles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were stationed in Gaza, Kibbutz Gaza, right not far from there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I got the ten-- nine trucks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we were advancing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But at the same time, supposedly, the English army was leaving those fortresses, the police stations.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "While I was advancing on the road, there were English tanks cruising around the area, back and forth, which wasn't such a pleasant feeling.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we felt that they were, like, on the Jordanian side.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When I advanced towards the main road, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which I was approaching [INAUDIBLE]-- this was the name of the area-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] which we had also on the left side of the road was a full brigade, volunteers from the United States, which they were digged in to cover us.",
      "word_count": 59
    }
  ],
